+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S3-P01-T031 (minimal Official Connector Interface / SDK; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Thirty-first task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the FIRST of S3 (China A0 Official Pilot -- replacing Board-3 news noise with A0 central-government official original text). Goal: a minimal, dependency-free Official Connector interface with exactly the pilot's capabilities (discover, fetch, verify, normalize, attachments, cursor, health), a typed contract, and an adapter registry -- with no business UI, no knowledge graph, and no new-platform coupling. NOT_DEPLOYED: this is the SDK; nothing is wired into the worker or D1 yet. Per an explicit Owner decision (connect real fetching at the kernel stage), the kernel's fetch is a genuine stdlib HTTP GET. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/official_connector.py (a stdlib-only OfficialConnector ABC with the seven capabilities, frozen typed dataclasses, a real HttpFetcher, an AdapterRegistry, and a run_chain full-chain driver), CONNECTOR_SDK_SPEC.md, and evidence/ADP-S3-P01-T031/real_fetch_smoke.json. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S3-P01-T031/test-results/connector_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): a MockOfficialConnector passes the full chain (health ok, discover two items, and for each fetch then verify marking the official .gov.cn domain as A0, then normalize extracting the document number 国发〔2026〕1号, the date 2026-01-05, the status 现行有效, and one attachment for the first document, then advance the cursor to the latest date 2026-02-10); the registry rejects a duplicate source_id; the SDK is stdlib-only with no requests/flask/django/networkx/neo4j/fastapi coupling; and HttpFetcher performs a real HTTP GET verified against a local loopback server returning the exact payload and matching sha256 (deterministic, no external network in CI). A separate live smoke fetched the real www.gov.cn (200, 67662 bytes, official domain, title 中国政府网_中央人民政府门户网站) and gov.cn/zhengce (200, 39811 bytes, title 政策_中国政府网) through the same HttpFetcher, recorded as a point-in-time, non-byte-reproducible artifact. The live smoke ran from the dev environment (not the worker), so 0 cloud cost; once A0 adapters (T034+) are wired into the worker cron, each fetch is a Worker subrequest counted against the DIR-007 free tier. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
